<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>About City Weather Explorer</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="dashboard">
      <section class="dashboard__header">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Project Dataset</p>
          <h1>About City Weather Explorer</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            This Rails application uses imported weather data to compare daily conditions
            across cities and show how each city connects to its historical records.
          </p>
        </div>
        <nav class="page-tabs" aria-label="Primary navigation">
          <%= link_to "Dashboard", root_path, class: "page-tab" %>
          <%= link_to "Countries", countries_path, class: "page-tab" %>
          <%= link_to "About", about_path, class: "page-tab page-tab--active" %>
        </nav>
      </section>

      <section class="metric-grid" aria-label="Dataset summary">
        <article class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-card__label">Cities</span>
          <strong><%= @city_count %></strong>
        </article>

        <article class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-card__label">Weather Records</span>
          <strong><%= @weather_record_count %></strong>
        </article>

        <article class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-card__label">Date Range</span>
          <% if @earliest_recorded_on && @latest_recorded_on %>
            <strong class="metric-card__compact"><%= @earliest_recorded_on %> to <%= @latest_recorded_on %></strong>
          <% else %>
            <strong>No data</strong>
          <% end %>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="about-grid">
        <article class="content-panel">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>Dataset</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            The project stores city records and daily weather observations. Each weather record
            includes a date, high temperature, low temperature, mean temperature, precipitation,
            maximum wind speed, and a weather condition code.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-panel">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>Data Source</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            Weather observations come from the Open-Meteo Historical Weather API, a public
            non-Faker data source. The importer requests daily weather values for selected city
            coordinates and saves the response in the Rails database.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="content-panel erd-panel">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2>Database ERD</h2>
          <p>City records have a one-to-many relationship with daily weather records.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="erd-diagram" aria-label="Database entity relationship diagram">
          <article class="erd-entity">
            <h3>cities</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>id</strong> primary key</li>
              <li>name</li>
              <li>country</li>
              <li>latitude</li>
              <li>longitude</li>
              <li>timezone</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <div class="erd-relation" aria-label="one city has many weather records">
            <span>1</span>
            <strong>has many</strong>
            <span>*</span>
          </div>

          <article class="erd-entity">
            <h3>weather_records</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>id</strong> primary key</li>
              <li><strong>city_id</strong> foreign key</li>
              <li>recorded_on</li>
              <li>temperature_max</li>
              <li>temperature_min</li>
              <li>temperature_mean</li>
              <li>precipitation_sum</li>
              <li>wind_speed_max</li>
              <li>weather_code</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
